com.nerjal.json

Class JsonParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nerjal.json.JsonParser

  • public abstract class JsonParser
extends Object
    Default class for parsing JSON both way.
    All comments contained in the root of a JSON string being parsed to a JsonElement will be put in the main element of the JSON string. Thus, the main element can only be a container element (so an Array or an Object). All other root element will result on a JsonError.JsonParseException
    However, all JsonElement can be parsed to a string, that being used for recursive parsing of container JsonElements


    Use stringify(JsonElement) and derivatives in order to parse a JSON structure to a String object. 

     using
     String s = JsonParser.parseJson(jsonObject);
 gives
     {
       "key": [value],
       ...
     }

    Using jsonify(String) allows to get the JsonElement of the given string. 

     using
     JsonElement jElem = JsonParser.parseString("{"a":["a",1,true]}");
 gives
     JsonObject[ "a": JsonArray[ JsonString["a"], JsonNumber[1], JsonBoolean[true]]]
    Since:
    JDK 16
    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    nerjal

      • jsonify

        public static JsonElement jsonify(String s)
                           throws JsonError.JsonParseException
        Parses a string to a JsonElement. The JsonElement type will depend on the String content.
        Warning: all null value will be considered as a null JsonString
        Parameters:
        s - String: the String to parse
        Returns:
        the parsed JsonElement. Can be an instance of any class implementing JsonElement
        Throws:
        JsonError.JsonParseException - if the given string cannot be parsed (missing quotes, braces, commas...)
